# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for `make tsan` (Stage 5, LAT-457).
#
# Scope discipline: only document-and-suppress races that are OUTSIDE the
# crystal-by-reference concurrency story; everything CbR-related must be
# fixed, not suppressed. Keep each entry annotated with a ticket reference.
#
# (The PIC data races flagged by the Stage 5 inventory were fixed by making PIC
# entries relaxed-atomic packed words — see include/inline_cache.h — and the
# LatRef cell races by LAT-450's per-cell lock + atomic refcount.)
#
# LAT-542 lock-order-inversion (NOT a data race — a documented-safe false
# positive). The nested-Ref two-cell mutation path (refchain_cross -> ref_lock)
# locks per-cell mutexes in chain order, which differs between threads
# (`a[0][1]=` locks A then B; `b[0][1]=` locks B then A — see the
# ref_lat542_abba_two_cell_no_deadlock probe). TSan reports a potential
# deadlock, but it cannot occur: refchain_cross takes the process-wide
# g_refchain_lock BEFORE any cell lock, serializing every multi-cell ref
# navigation, so the per-cell acquisition order can never interleave across
# threads. Single-cell ref_lock callers cannot invert (one lock). Suppressing
# the lock-order heuristic here is sound; the gate lock is the real invariant.
deadlock:ref_lock
